Recap of OOP Concepts

Class → har problem ek class me solve.

Attributes/Properties → jaise self.text, self.people, self.number.

Methods → count_words, make_change, calculate, etc.

Inheritance → HandheldCalculator → SimpleCalculator se inherit.

Encapsulation → har class apna data andar rakhti hai.

Polymorphism → override method (calculate vs calculate_and_store).


📝 Explanation (Easy Language)

Class: har problem ke liye ek class banayi.

Properties (Attributes): data store karne ke liye (jaise self.text, self.number, etc.).

Methods: functions jo object kaam karte hain (count_words, make_change, etc.).

Inheritance: HandheldCalculator → inherits from SimpleCalculator (uses super() to reuse code).

Encapsulation: har class ka apna data internally handle hota hai.

Polymorphism: override kiya calculate method ko ek aur class me (advanced concept).